This is the art-web cvs module, the php code that runs art.gnome.org.  If you need to make a change to
the site, please let me <thos@gnome.org> know first before you check anything in.  Thanks.

Setup Guide
---------------------------------
1. Checkout the art-web cvs module.
     cvs -d :pserver:anonymous@anoncvs.gnome.org:/cvs/gnome login
     # Hit enter when prompted for a password
     cvs -d :pserver:anonymous@anoncvs.gnome.org:/cvs/gnome co art-web

2. Create the images/ directory
     cd art-web
     mkdir images/

3. Download the images archive.
     cd images
     wget -c http://www.gnome.org/~thos/art-web/ago-images.tar.bz2
     tar xvjf art-images.tar.bz2

4. Create the MySQL database, download and import the initial schema.
     wget http://www.gnome.org/~thos/art-web/art-web-structure.sql
     mysql # You may need -u <username>, and -p options to authenticate.
     > CREATE DATABASE artweb;
     > QUIT
     mysql < art-web-structure.sql

5. Create includes/mysql.inc.php to provide connection details, with the 
   following contents.
     <?php
      mysql_connect("localhost","user","password");
      mysql_select_db("artweb");
     ?>

6. Setup Apache with the following options - this varies depending on
   distribution, so I can't provide definitive locations. It'll probably
   be somewhere around /etc/apache2/

   <Directory /path/to/art-web/>
     AllowOverride None
     order allow,deny
     allow from all

     php_value include_path .:/path/to/art-web/includes:/usr/share/php
     DirectoryIndex index.html index.php
     <FilesMatch "(backgrounds|themes|gtk_engines|art-icons|download|users|contest)">
       ForceType application/x-httpd-php
     </FilesMatch>
   </Directory>
